In December 2019, a new coronavirus, 2019 (2019-nCovV), now officially known as coronavirus 2019 (COVID-19), broke out, and the virus itself was called severe acute respiratory syndrome 2 (SARS-COV-2).
On March 11, 2020, WHO classified COVID-19 as a pandemic.
